<BYLINE>By DENISE BEZICK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>INDIANAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Indiana </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> reached a tentative contract agreement Tuesday night with the union representing 4,200 striking telephone workers, bringing parent company <ORGANIZATION> Ameritech </ORGANIZATION> closer to ending a 17-day-old strike. The three-year pact between <ORGANIZATION> Indiana </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> made <ORGANIZATION> Michigan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> the only one of five subsidiaries of <ORGANIZATION> Ameritech </ORGANIZATION>, a regional `` Baby Bell'' company, without a contract agreement. The <ORGANIZATION> CWA </ORGANIZATION> has instructed all 37,000 members in <LOCATION> Ameritech </LOCATION> territory to stay off the job until agreements are reached with all five companies. Tentative settlements were reached over the weekend with <ORGANIZATION> Ohio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Wisconsin </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION>, and on Monday with <ORGANIZATION> Illinois </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION>. Talks with <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bell </LOCATION> resumed Tuesday, and continued early Wednesday, said spokesmen for the utility and the union. The <ORGANIZATION> Indiana </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> agreement was announced by the utility and the union. A ratification vote must be held within 45 days of strikers' returning to work Until strikers return, the company will continue operating with management and supervisory personnel, said <ORGANIZATION> Indiana </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Estel </PERSON> <PERSON> Gibson </PERSON>. The Ameritech walkout began Aug. 13, seven days after strikes began at three other regional