</ORGANIZATION> chairman, <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>, and <LOCATION> Iraqi </LOCATION> leaders. He has been trying to revive a stalled Arab League peace effort. After the fighting broke out in March, <PERSON> Aoun </PERSON> declared a `` war of liberation'' to drive the Syrians out of <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. The troops came under a 1976 Arab League peacekeeping mandate, but <PERSON> Aoun </PERSON> says they are really backing the Moslems in the nation's 14-year-old civil war.
