<HEAD>Bus Plunges Off Mountain Road, 35 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAIDU SHARIF, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A bus drove off a mountain road and plunged 500 feet into a ravine, killing 35 people, police said. The accident took place near the mountain village of <LOCATION> Shahpur </LOCATION> in the Swat valley, 100 miles northwest of <LOCATION> Islamabad </LOCATION>, the capital, police said. The bus was on a regular mountain run between the villages of <LOCATION> Alipuri </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Alandar </LOCATION> when it swerved on a sharp curve and plunged over the edge. Police said 35 passengers died instantly, five others survived with injuries. Their conditions were not immediately disclosed. <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION>'s northern areas have been soaked with monsoon rains recently, but police said they did not know if weather was a factor in the bus crash.
