<BYLINE>BY ELOY O. AGUILAR</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The government kept secret the formula it will unveil this week for a new administration, but it increased security throughout <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> on Wednesday in anticipation of violent demonstrations. Officials of the current administration have made clear that the new government will be announced and will take office on Friday, when the term of Acting President <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Solis </PERSON> expires. It will have the blessing of Gen. <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, who as commander of the Panamanian Defense Forces is the power behind the civilian administration. The Defense Forces include both soldiers and police. Paramilitary groups organized into national defense committees trained in different sites throughout the capital on Wednesday and government agencies said they were placing themselves on a state of alert. Opposition leaders said they planned no street protests against the installation of a new government on Friday. `` If anything happens, it will be spontaneous,'' said former opposition presidential candidate <PERSON> Guillermo </PERSON> <PERSON> Endara </PERSON> in an interview Wednesday. `` Nothing special is going to happen on Friday. The government will change some figures and will retain others.'' <PERSON> Endara </PERSON> claims he won the May 7 elections, which were annulled by the government. The opposition refused a government offer to form a national reconciliation government. The government rejected opposition demands that its victory be recognized and that <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> step down. Government officials said all formulas were being considered in the formation of the new government. However, sources, speaking on the condition of anonymity, said it appeared the new government would consist of a junta with civilian and military representatives. The governemnt scheduled a special Cabinet session for Thursday morning. A special session of the <ORGANIZATION>