<HEAD>Attorney Says Defendant in Lesbian Slaying Trial Feared for Her Life</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SANDRA WALEWSKI</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A woman who contends she killed her lesbian lover because she was a victim of `` battered spouse syndrome'' had been abused for years and feared for her life, her lawyer said at her trial Wednesday. <PERSON> Annette </PERSON> <PERSON> Green </PERSON>, 30, was beaten and tormented for 11 years before she fired a .38 - caliber pistol into the head of <PERSON> Ivonne </PERSON> <PERSON> Julio </PERSON>, 32, after a Halloween party last year, said defense attorney <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Lasley </PERSON> hopes to introduce expert testimony at the murder trial to prove she suffered from battered spouse syndrome and acted in self-defense. Attorneys for both sides believe the trial is one of the first in which the syndrome defense, usually employed in cases involving long-term abusive heterosexual relationships, has been applied in one involving a homosexual union. Ms. <PERSON> Green </PERSON>'s love for Ms. <PERSON> Julio </PERSON>'s teen-age twin daughters kept her from ending the stormy relationship, <PERSON> Lasley </PERSON> said during a break in the first day of testimony Wednesday. `` For 11 years, she was the mother of -LRB- Ms. <PERSON> Julio </PERSON>'s -RRB- twins and performed the domestic duties of the relationship,'' <PERSON> Lasley </PERSON> said. `` She was frequently battered and abused physically and psychologically, along with the children.'' Judge <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Waddell </PERSON> is expected to rule next week whether to allow experts to testify about battered spouse syndrome. Assistant State Attorney <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON> has said he'll challenge any attempt to bring the syndrome into the case because, he said, there is no research involving homosexual relationships. The prosecution maintains that Ms. <PERSON> Julio </PERSON> was killed while she was in the closet of the mobile home the women shared. `` <PERSON> Ivonne </PERSON> <PERSON> Julio </PERSON> was down on her knees in the closet beggi