 A meeting of the central committee of the <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Churches </ORGANIZATION> accepted a new member, the <ORGANIZATION> Kiribati </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Protestant </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION>. It has 31,000 members, about half the population of the 33 <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pacific </LOCATION> islands making up republic of <LOCATION> Kiribati </LOCATION>. The admission brought to 307 the number of the council's <ORGANIZATION> Protestant </ORGANIZATION> and Eastern Orthodox member denominations Their memberships total more than 400 million.
