<HEAD>With AM-Helmsley Trial, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The following is the verdict brought Wednesday against <PERSON> Leona </PERSON> <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON> and her co-defendants, <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Turco </PERSON> and <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Licari </PERSON>: Count 1 _ Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>, <PERSON> Turco </PERSON> and <PERSON> Licari </PERSON>, convicted of conspiracy to defraud the <ORGANIZATION> Internal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revenue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> in 1983-85. Count 2 _ Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>, convicted of tax evasion in 1983. Count 3 _ Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>, convicted of tax evasion in 1984. Count 4 _ Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>, convicted of tax evasion in 1985. Count 5 _ <PERSON> Licari </PERSON> and <PERSON> Turco </PERSON>, convicted of aiding and abetting tax evasion in 1983. Count 6 _ <PERSON> Licari </PERSON> and <PERSON> Turco </PERSON>, convicted of aiding and abetting tax evasion in 1984. Count 7 _ <PERSON> Licari </PERSON> and <PERSON> Turco </PERSON>, convicted of aiding and abetting tax evasion in 1986. Count 8 _ Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>, convicted of making and subscribing false personal tax returns in 1983. Count 9 _ Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>, convicted of making and subscribing false personal tax returns in 1984. Count 10 _ Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>, convicted of making and subscribing false personal tax returns in 1985. Count 11 _ <PERSON> Licari </PERSON> and <PERSON> Turco </PERSON>, convicted of aiding and assisting the filing of false personal tax returns in 1983. Count 12 _ <PERSON> Licari </PERSON> and <PERSON> Turco </PERSON>, convicted of aiding and assisting in filing false personal tax returns in 1984. Count 13 _ <PERSON> Licari </PERSON> and <PERSON> Turco </PERSON>, convicted of aiding and assisting in filing false personal tax returns in 1985. Counts 14-29 _ Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>, <PERSON> Licari </PERSON> and <PERSON> Turco </PERSON>, convicted of aiding and assisting in the filing of false returns for businesses in the <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON> organization. Counts 30-39 _ Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>, <PERSON> Licari </PERSON> and <PERSON> Turco </PERSON>, convicted of mail fraud as part of a scheme to defraud the state <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Taxation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Finance </ORGANIZATION> by filing false state income tax returns. Counts 40-46 _ Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON>, <PERSON> Licari </PERSON> and <PERSON> Turco </PERSON>, acquitted of mail fraud as part of a scheme to defraud minority shareholders of a Helmsley-controlled partnership. Count 47 _ Mrs. <PERSON> Helmsley </PERSON> and <PERSON> Turco </PERSON>, acquitted of extortion conspiracy to get kickbacks from vendors.
